In this exercise, you will foster your creativity and again practice the connection between your brain, eye, and hand. 

Materials:
- Paper 
- Crayons
- India Ink
- Needle or something sharp

Take a paper and color the interior panel, with any pattern you would like. Leave at least one inch margins. After thickly coloring,
coat it with India ink, and dry it well. Make sure it is super dry! Then take something sharp and start drawing! You will see the 
color revealed underneath. 
